## 2. The Big Risk In Usage‑Based Pricing = Your Edge Story

- Procurement’s fear:
  - Usage‑based works when value tracks usage, but buyers struggle when they **can’t predict monthly costs**, which creates procurement pushback and anxiety. [zylo](https://zylo.com/blog/a-new-trend-in-saas-pricing-enter-the-usage-based-model/)
  - Over time, some customers under‑use the product just to avoid surprise bills, which **caps your upside** if you don’t manage it. [nxcode](https://www.nxcode.io/resources/news/saas-pricing-strategy-guide-2026)
- Blind spots your competitors create:
  - SaaS buyers are being told that the shift to usage‑based introduces **budget volatility and blind spots** in their SaaS management programs. [zylo](https://zylo.com/blog/a-new-trend-in-saas-pricing-enter-the-usage-based-model/)
  - They’re warned to invest in **usage visibility, budgeting controls, and alerting** to keep this from turning into chaos. [zylo](https://zylo.com/blog/a-new-trend-in-saas-pricing-enter-the-usage-based-model/)
- Why that’s a gift:
  - Tap919 Middleman + AetherDesk can be framed as:
    - “The **visibility layer** for all AI usage.”
    - “A seat at the table when CFOs ask ‘What are we spending on AI?’”

**Move:** In 120 days, make sure you can demo:
- Per‑tenant:
  - Monthly spend trajectory.
  - “If you keep going like this, next bill will be ≈ X.”
- Per‑model:
  - Which `tap919:` lanes are yielding the best **value per dollar**.
  - Strong, human‑readable cost breakdowns.

You’re not just selling usage; you’re selling **predictability in an unpredictable pricing world**. [stripe](https://stripe.com/resources/more/usage-based-pricing-strategy-for-saas)

