## 3. Credits, Tiers, And Hybrid Models Are The Sweet Spot

- Credits and tiers are trending:
  - Current guides highlight **prepaid credits**, **tiered usage bands**, and **hybrid models** (base fee + usage) as the dominant patterns. [schematichq](https://schematichq.com/blog/why-usage-based-billing-is-taking-over-saas)
  - Tiered usage plans (0–10k units, 10k–100k, etc.) with different per‑unit pricing in each band are used to encourage growth without scary jumps. [schematichq](https://schematichq.com/blog/why-usage-based-billing-is-taking-over-saas)
- When usage‑based works best:
  - Works when:
    - Value clearly correlates with usage.
    - Customers’ usage is variable.
    - Low barrier to entry is important (pay‑as‑you‑go). [zignuts](https://www.zignuts.com/blog/usage-based-pricing-saas)
  - Breaks when:
    - Bills are opaque.
    - Variability is too high and buyers can’t plan. [nxcode](https://www.nxcode.io/resources/news/saas-pricing-strategy-guide-2026)
- Why that matters for your lanes:
  - You want *both*:
    - Cheap, obvious on‑ramps (“buy 100k tokens for $X”).
    - The ability to scale to big contracts with predictable spend.

**Move:** For day 0 pricing:
- Make `tap919` credits:
  - 1 credit ≈ some number of tokens / requests.
- Offer:
  - **Freemium band** (e.g., 0–10k tokens free / month).
  - **Prepaid blocks** (e.g., 1M token packs with discounts).
  - **Commit + overage** for agencies and enterprises.

Design all of this so it flows directly from Middleman’s `UsageEvent` logs; no separate billing logic. [zignuts](https://www.zignuts.com/blog/usage-based-pricing-saas)

