- Optimize pricing mix:
  - Shifting ~20% of customers from Starter to Growth/Enterprise tiers produces a **disproportionate lift** in revenue without big overhead spikes. [financialmodelslab](https://financialmodelslab.com/blogs/profitability/api-monetization)
  - For Tap919:
    - Move agencies from “just using one lane” to bundles (agents + CRISPR + analytics).
- Reduce core COGS:
  - Cutting infra costs (cloud hosting, data transfer) from 80% to 60% of revenue increases gross margin. [financialmodelslab](https://financialmodelslab.com/blogs/profitability/api-monetization)
  - For Tap919:
    - Negotiate better rates.
    - Use local/in‑house models where margin is best.
    - Use routing agents to auto‑optimize spend.
- Increase enterprise setup/value fees:
  - Raising enterprise setup fees (e.g., from 5k to 10k) provides upfront cash and filters to serious accounts. [financialmodelslab](https://financialmodelslab.com/blogs/profitability/api-monetization)
  - For you:
    - Charge “implementation / lane design” fees when you deeply integrate agents for a big client.
- Improve funnel efficiency:
  - Focusing on trial‑to‑paid conversion is a high‑ROI lever, because it effectively lowers CAC. [financialmodelslab](https://financialmodelslab.com/blogs/profitability/api-monetization)
  - For you:
    - Use StreetCode + Middleman to auto‑generate “guided trials” where you show:
      - Real usage.
      - Predicted savings.
